Manual test steps — Champion's Bounty on Harpoon/Blood Rain

Champion's Bounty is a random global event, so you'll need to get lucky or temporarily force it. The simplest approach: start multiple games until the event is drawn.

Setup

Start the server: ./server.exe
Open two browser tabs, join the same game room (1v1)
Wait for the game to show the event banner — look for Champion's Bounty at the top
If the wrong event comes up, end the game and start another. (FFA3/FFA5 would be ideal since Champion's Bounty only applies in FFA modes — check OnKillBountyCards() returns 0 for all modes or if it's mode-gated. Actually looking at the handler, it always returns 2 — it's not mode-gated in the code. So 1v1 works too.)

Harpoon test

During the Buy phase, buy or acquire a Harpoon and a Dragon warrior
On your Attack phase, place the Dragon on the field
Ensure the opponent has a Dragon on their field
Use the Harpoon on the opponent's Dragon — kill it (it has 8 HP, Harpoon deals 8 on a Dragon)
Expected: Champion's Bounty notification appears (top of screen or notification), and your hand grows by 2 cards
Blood Rain test

Acquire a Blood Rain card and have warriors in the enemy field
On your Attack phase, use Blood Rain on the enemy field
Kill at least one enemy warrior
Expected: Champion's Bounty notification appears and 2 cards are drawn
Negative test — dragon survives

Use Harpoon on a Dragon that has more than 8 HP (e.g. one that has been healed or has a buff)
Expected: No Champion's Bounty notification, no extra cards drawn


Bloodlust on Archer Instant Kill
Setup:

./server.exe — open two browser tabs, join the same room
Wait until the event banner shows Bloodlust (or restart games until it appears)
During the Buy phase, get an Archer warrior and a Special Power card into your hand/field
Happy path — target killed:

Enter the Attack phase — place Archer on your field
Use the Special Power on an enemy warrior
Expected: The Archer's HP badge increases by +2 (the attacker heals, not all field warriors)
The history log shows the special power action
Negative — target survives (if applicable — instant kill always kills, but test no-Bloodlust):

Do the same with a Calm or any non-Bloodlust event
Expected: Archer HP is unchanged after the kill
Key distinction from Harpoon/Blood Rain: only the Archer itself heals — not every warrior on your field.

Champion's Bounty on Archer Instant Kill
Champion's Bounty is only drawn in FFA3 or FFA5 game modes.

Setup:

Start an FFA3 or FFA5 game (at least 3 browser tabs)
Wait until the event banner shows Champion's Bounty
Get an Archer + Special Power card
Identify which enemy player has the most total field HP (the HP sum shown next to the player name)
Happy path — kill the top enemy:

In your Attack phase, use Special Power on a warrior belonging to the player with the highest field HP total
The instant kill succeeds (HP → 0)
Expected:
Your hand grows by 2 cards
History log shows a "Champion's Bounty" entry
result.Attack.ChampionsBountyEarner = your player name, ChampionsBountyCards = number drawn
Negative — target is NOT the top enemy:

Use Special Power on a warrior from the player with lower total field HP
Expected: No extra cards drawn, no bounty history entry
Negative — target survives:

Not possible for instant kill (it always kills), but verify the Calm event scenario: no bounty, no heal


